        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter">
                    <ab><title>Numbers 16</title>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                        <l><emph>Parashat Korach</emph></l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                        <l n="1">And Korah, son
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                            of Izhar, son of Kohath, son of Levi, and Dathan
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                            and Abiram, sons of Eliab, and On,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                            son of Peleth, sons of Reuben, took an advice:</l>
                        <l n="2">
                            <milestone unit="page" n="239v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                            And they rose up before Moses — and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                            two hundred and fifty men of the children of Israel: princes of the
                            congregation, representatives of the appointed time,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                            men of renown.</l>
                        <l n="3">And they gathered themselves against Moses
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                            and against Aaron, and said to them, ‘It is enough for you
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                            that all the congregation are holy, every one of them, and among them
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                            is the divine Presence of the Lord. And why do you exalt yourself
                            against the assembly
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                            of the Lord?’</l>
                        <l n="4">And Moses heard it, and he fell
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                            on his face:</l>
                        <l n="5">And he spoke to Korah and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                            to all his congregation, saying, ‘At dawn the Lord will make known
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                            who is his and who is more holy, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                            he will cause him to come near to him. And he will cause the one he
                            chooses to come near
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                            to him.</l>
                        <l n="6">Do this: Take you censers,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                            Korah and all his congregation,</l>
                        <l n="7">And put
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                            fire in them, and set incense on them before
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                            the Lord at daybreak. And it shall be that the man whom the Lord will chose,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                            he will be holy. You have enough, oh sons of Levi.’</l>
                        <l n="8">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                            Moses said to Korah, ‘Hear, now, you, sons of Levi:</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                        <l n="9">Is it too small |a thing| to you that the God of Israel has separated
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                            you from the congregation of Israel, to bring you near to himself to do
                            the service
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                            of the tabernacle of the Lord, and to stand
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                            before the congregation to minister to them?</l>
                        <l n="10">
                            <milestone unit="page" n="240r" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                            And he has brought you near to him, and all your brothers the sons of Levi
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                            with you. And you want the priesthood as well?</l>
                        <l n="11">Therefore
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                            you and all the congregation who are gathering are against the Lord!
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                            And what is Aaron that you murmur against him?’</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                        <l n="12">And Moses sent to call Dathan and Abiram,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                            sons of Eliab, and they said, ‘We will not go.</l>
                        <l n="13">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                            Is it |a| small |thing| that you have brought us out from a land flowing
                            |with| milk and honey
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                            to kill us in the wilderness, that you lord it over
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                            us as well, to lord it over?</l>
                        <l n="14">Moreover
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                            you have not brought us to a land flowing |with| milk and honey, and you
                            have not given us
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                            the portion of fields and vineyards. Will you put out the eyes of these men?
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                            We will not be able to go to that land because of the heroism
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                            of the Anakites.’</l>
                        <l n="15">And Moses was very angry,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                            and he said to the Lord, ‘Do not turn to their grain offering. Not
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                            one donkey have I taken from them for the burden, and I have not done evil
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                            to any of them.’</l>
                        <l n="16">And Moses said to Korah,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                            ‘Be you and all your congregation before the Lord, you, and they, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                            Aaron, at dawn.</l>
                        <l n="17">And take every man his censer, and put
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                            incense on them, and bring before the Lord each man
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                            his censer, two hundred and fifty censers, and you and Aaron,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                            each man his censer.’</l>
                        <l n="18">And each man took his censer, and
                            <milestone unit="page" n="240v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                            put fire on them and laid incense on them,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                            and stood in the door of the tent of meeting, and Moses
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                            and Aaron.</l>
                        <l n="19">And Korah gathered all the congregation against them
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                            to the door of the tent of meeting, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                            the divine Presence of the Lord appeared to all the congregation.</l>
                        <l n="20">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                            the Lord spoke to Moses and to Aaron, saying,</l>
                        <l n="21">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                            ‘Separate yourselves from among this congregation, that I may consume
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                            them <seg type="commented" corresp="#seg001" />in the blink of an eye<anchor
                                type="commented" xml:id="seg001" /><ref target="#fn1"
                                type="noteAnchor" />.’</l>
                        <l n="22">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                            they fell on their faces, and said, ‘Oh God,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                            the God of the spirits, of the spirits of all flesh, will one
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                            man sin, and will you be angry at all the congregation?’</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                        <l n="23">And the Lord spoke to Moses, saying,</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                        <l n="24">Speak to the congregation, saying, ‘Get away from around
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                            the dwelling places of Korah, Dathan, and Abiram.’</l>
                        <l n="25">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                            And Moses rose up and went to Dathan and Abiram, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                            the elders of Israel followed him.</l>
                        <l n="26">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                            he spoke to the congregation, saying, ‘Get away, now,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                            from the tents of these wicked men, and do not touch anything
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                            that is theirs, lest you be destroyed by all their sins.’</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                        <l n="27">So they got away from the dwelling places of Korah,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                            Dathan, and Abiram, all around. And Dathan and Abiram came out,
                            <milestone unit="page" n="241r" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                            stood in the door of their tents, and their wives,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                            and their sons, and their little ones.</l>
                        <l n="28">And Moses said,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                            ‘Hereby you shall know that the Lord has sent me to do
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                            all these works, for I have not done them from my own heart.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                        <l n="29">If these men die as all men die,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                            or if they be cared after with the care of all men,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                            then the Lord has not sent me.</l>
                        <l n="30">But if
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                            the Lord makes a new thing, and the earth opens its mouth,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                            and swallows them up with all that belongs to them, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                            they go down alive to the deep grave, then you shall know that
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                            these men have made the Lord angry.’</l>
                        <l n="31">And it was
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                            as he was finishing speaking all these words,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                            and the ground that was under them broke up,</l>
                        <l n="32">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                            And the earth opened its mouth and swallowed them and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                            their households and all the men that belonged to Korah
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                            and all their goods.</l>
                        <l n="33">And they went down,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                            they and all that they had, alive to the deep grave. And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                            the earth covered them over, and they perished from among
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                            the assembly.</l>
                        <l n="34">And all Israel that were all around them
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                            fled at the cry of them, for they said, ‘Lest the earth swallow
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                            us up also.’</l>
                        <l n="35">And there came out a fire from before
                            <milestone unit="page" n="241v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                            the Lord, and consumed the two hundred and fifty men that brought forward
                            <milestone unit="line" xml:id="Num016-P241v-L2_trl" n="2" next="ADub.III.73.004.017.trl.xml#Num017-P241v-L2_trl" />
                            incense.</l>
                    </ab>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp>
                    <app>
                        <note xml:id="fn1" type="footnote">I.e., <emph>in an instant</emph>.</note>
                    </app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
